  if any(v == 3 for v in cnt):\n                return \"B\" if k & 1 else \"A\"\n        return \"Draw\" if n == 9 else \"Pending\"\n```\n\nThis code implements the solution by tracking the counts of 'X' and 'O' in rows, columns, and diagonals using an array `cnt`. It iterates through the moves in reverse order, checking if the last move (or the move before the last, depending on the turn) results in a win. If a win is detected, it returns the winner (\"A\" or \"B\"). If all moves are played and no winner is found, it returns \"Draw\". Otherwise, it returns \"Pending\" indicating the game is not yet over.", "estimated_date": 1575158400000}